reviews.text: Love this place so much and it has been our favourite place for breakfast or lunch since we discovered it. We love to visit during their off peak around 3pm to slowly enjoying our food and sipping their kopi üòãüëçAll dishes we ordered so far are so yummy ie fried kway teow, fried mamak mee, mee rebus, durian tempura, special secret Kueh,rojak, kaya butter toast, prawn mee, ipoh hor fun, kopi O, kopi c. Plenty of seats with different layout. Service is prompt and polite.Wide variety of food to choose from. Pricing is reasonable. Highly recommended üëç üëçüëçüòãüòãüòã

Passed by this place multiple times, but never gave it a chance until just recently. Ordered their rendang chicken rice & nasi lemak with chicken fillet. To my delight, both were well-presented, flavorful, and good portion. Their signature coffee is quite intense, but I got no complaints about that. This restaurant covers 2 shop lots which provide ample space for diners. Waiters were polite, and food were quick to be served. My only negative comment is the amount of flies there. I'd say this is an underrated restaurant; would come again.
